18 July 2016The Deputy Minister of Communications, Ms Stella Ndabeni Abrahams will, on Tuesday 19 July 2016, lead a youth information and career EXPO in Manyisane, Mqanduli.This programme is a response to a call made by the young people of Mqanduli who reached out to the Deputy Minister to bring information about the wide array of education, career and business opportunities available for youth in government, State Owned Entities (SOEs) and the private sector.Encouraged by the high skills shortage, unemployment and substance abuse in the area; the Deputy Minister heeded to this noble call. The multi-stakeholder EXPO will focus on:Members of the media are invited to be part of this community outreach programme which will take place as follows: Date: Tuesday, 19 July 2016 Venue: Manyisa Hall, Mqanduli, KSD Local Municipality Time: 9h30 14h00Journalists will be afforded interviews and photo opportunities.RSVP: Vuyani Sibene on 0735763381 or vuyani@gcis.gov.zaEnquiries: Ndlelantle Pinyana Cell: 076 142 8606Nthabeleng Mokitimi-Dlamini Cell: 073 222 5522Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of the Ministry of Communications